<h3>Building a Review System</h3>
<p>Most agents wait for reviews to appear organically. That approach produces 2 to 3 reviews per year. A systematic approach produces 2 to 3 per week.</p>
<p><strong>The insurance agent review system:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li><strong>After every policy sale</strong>, send a personalized review request email within 24 hours</li>
<li><strong>After every claim resolution</strong>, send a follow-up asking about their experience</li>
<li><strong>At annual renewals</strong>, request a review as part of your renewal check-in</li>
<li><strong>Make it easy</strong>. Send a direct link to your Google review form (not your GBP listing page)</li>
</ol>
<p>For detailed review-building tactics, see our guide on <a href="/blog/get-more-google-reviews-local-business/">how to get more Google reviews</a>.</p>
<h3>Responding to Reviews</h3>
<p>Respond to every review within 24 to 48 hours. Thank positive reviewers by name. For negative reviews, acknowledge the concern, take the conversation offline, and avoid sharing client details publicly. Our guide on <a href="/blog/respond-to-negative-google-reviews/">responding to negative reviews</a> covers the exact framework.</p>
